      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FICTION FILE (5) has her hoof on the till after placing in her last three outings, last week coming from the back row to finish runner-up at Ballarat. Goes well at this distance with a win and two placings from three attempts. Can break through. A wide draw poses more of a challenge for JANIEBQUICK (7) but her form is hard to knock having put together a string of placings before leading to score at Melton last week. If things go her way she could strike again. CALEDONIAN RANGER (4) has been freshened since he missed by just a head last start at Warragul. Go well. MONSIEUR FLAMEL (3) draws well and could be close to a win after back-to-back placings, the latest from a wider barrier at Cranbourne.",
